A=\log r
B=\log s
r+s
r=e^A
s=e^B
r+s=e^A+e^B
\log(r+s)=\log(e^A+e^B)
\log(e^A+e^B)
b
r+s
\log(X+Y)=\log X+\log(1+b^{\log Y-\log X})
A+\log(1+b^{B-A})
\log(b^A+b^B)=\log(b^A(1+b^{B-A}))=\log b^A+\log(1+b^{B-A})=A+\log(1+b^{B-A})
A = \log a
B = \log b
\log(a + b) = \log(e^A + e^B)
A + \log(1 + e^{B-A})
B + \log(1 + e^{A-B})
